genresAdvancedInfo.name: korean musicals
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Korean musicals are a popular form of musical theater in South Korea. They often feature a fusion of traditional Korean music and contemporary pop music, with elaborate sets and costumes. The stories are usually based on historical events or popular Korean dramas, and are known for their emotional depth and powerful performances.
